Business Brief -- Havas S.A.:
   French Group's Net Income
   Fell About 9% During 1991
In addition, the group said it expects tourism operations
to move out of the red this year, while the contribution from
the profits of pay television affiliate Canal Plus S.A. is
seen growing at a satisfactory pace. Havas owns 25% of Canal
Plus.
   Havas said it expects 1992 net profit to rebound back to
around 1.15 billion francs.
   Revenue rose 12% to 26.5 billion francs from 23.7 billion
francs. The gain was only 6.5%, however, on a comparable
structural and exchange-rate basis. Foreign sales accounted
for 30% of the total, up from 24% in 1990.